{
  "stem": "18670.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 234.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "These are not private homes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They would see the superintendent and ask him, do you have any complaints about any of the Jews in your building?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And if he had complaints, they would get these people out on the street, beat them up.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Or it was winter time.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of the things that they really loved to do and it happened to a cousin of ours, roll up your pants-- and some people wear long johns, roll up the long johns, then they spill lye on the sidewalk, now scrub the sidewalk.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the lye would eat right into the skin, down to the flesh.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Or they beat them up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Or they marched them, especially when Jews, religious Jews with the beards, that was a great joy to them to have them march, throw rotten eggs at them, spit on them, you know.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 83,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The fear always was that they would come in those command cars, they called them, that the police used when they wanted to block off a street when there was a riot or something like that in pre-Hitler days.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now the Nazis used that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They would block of a whole street and round up Jewish people, like questioning them to identify them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was caught in one of those one day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I realized it was on the Taborstrasse in 2nd District.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I knew the area was [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was a-- I don't know what you call it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was actually a connection between Taborstrasse and next street, through an apartment building, that you could walk through and get out on the other side.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that's the way I escaped.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 84,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I saw them pick people out of the lineups at the different embassies in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
